<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>{% if svc == "dav-anon" %}Anonymous {% endif %}WebDAV Service Landing Page</title>
    <base href="/{{ svc }}/"/>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  </head>

  <body>
    <h1>
      CyVerse Data Store{% if svc == "dav-anon" %} Anonymous, Read-Only{% endif %} WebDAV Access
    </h1>

    <p>
      The CyVerse Data Store has four{% if svc == "dav-anon" %} anonymous, read-only{% endif %}
      WebDAV services.{% if svc != "dav-anon" %} If a request is authenticated, the autheticated
      user's permissions will determine what data can be read or modified. Providing
      <code>anonymous</code> as the user name and no password will grant anonymous access.
      {% endif %}
    </p>

    <p>Here are the four services.</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ _irods_zone_name }}/commons/community_released/">Community released data access</a>
        provides access to public data hosted at CyVerse but curated by community members.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ _irods_zone_name }}/commons/cyverse_curated/">CyVerse curated data access</a>
        provides access to public data hosted at CyVerse and curated here.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ _irods_zone_name }}/projects/">Project data access</a> provides access to
        project data hosted at CyVerse.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ _irods_zone_name }}/home/">User data access</a> provides access to user data
        hosted at CyVerse. In order to reduce the risk of user data inadvertently being exposed to
        web crawlers, <code>/{{ _irods_zone_name }}/home</code> and all of its immediate folders,
        i.e., folders of the form <code>/{{ _irods_zone_name }}/home/<em>folder</em></code> where
        <em>folder</em> is the name of a folder under <code>home</code>, will not be
        accessible{% if svc != "dav-anon" %} without authentication{% endif %}.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
